In another aspect of the above process:


(a) a solution in aqueous acid of the 2-pyridylethyl-di-(lower alkyl) malonate is heated to prepare a solution of the pyridyl acid in aqueous acid;


(b) a catalyst is added to the solution of pyridyl acid and the mixture is treated with hydrogen to form a mixture of catalyst and the piperidine acid;


(c) the catalyst is separated the from the mixture to prepare an aqueous solution of piperidine acid; and


(d) base and a N-protecting agent are added to the aqueous solution to prepare the N-protected piperidine acid.

